  "text": "With regard to the type of assessment, [CITATION_1] suggested that high self-esteem participants may express biases on all types of measures while low selfesteem participants are more likely to express bias on implicit measures. Our fi ndings provide some support for this proposition: On the one hand, on explicit measures like trait ratings, adolescents expressed feelings and readiness for social contact; on the other hand, on implicit measures, adolescents expressed strong and consistent bias (Bar-Tal & Teichman, 2005 ) .",
